text:
Hey Goob, I wanted to talk just a little about the "test results" you got. First, please make sure you don't put too much stock in random online quiz results; there's not much credibility in them-often very little-and anything important like that really needs to be discussed with a doctor, or other licensed professional. If a quiz like that motivates you to go out and do that, that's fine, but you never need to stress about it on its own. Believe me, I've been there before; my anxiety has pushed me to try to internet diagnose myself, and it never helps me feel less worried.

That said though, if you're just curious about that stuff, and how it might be something you can relate to, that's perfectly okay! It can be reassuring learning about stuff that could apply to you, even if you never decide to do anything about it. But if you feel like there's something about the way you think or act that's causing you problems or stress in life, please know you always deserve the chance to speak to someone about how to manage it. It takes an incredible amount of courage to do, so you should be proud of it, and it's never ever too late to do so.

All that aside though, please always remember: you are truly wonderful and deserving of love the way you are, no matter what goes on in your little shark brain of whether or not you understand any of it. You've made a place where lots of people (hopefully including you) can feel comfortable and have fun, no matter what kind of weird we may be.

Anyway, enough ranting about serious stuff. I've missed a whole lot of streams lively lately cause life too busy, but watching all the Stanley shenanigans was still absolutely hilarious. I'm super excited for your birthday, especially cause I'll be able to afford merch this time! Hope you're doin well Goob, love ya little weirdo!
